te SocialProof.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create CallToAction.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create Footer.tsx component\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Assemble IndexPage.tsx with all components\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Verify all files are created correctly\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"}]\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01QtpvCruRxCXhm6uTtSAke3\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01K9nve8xGoXqSAfqGe9bcSz\",\"name\":\"task\",\"input\":{\"subagent_type\":\"copywriter\",\"description\":\"Draft compelling copy for the HERO section of a landing page.\\n\\nCONTEXT:\\n- Product: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones\\n- Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents. Project managers tired of endless Slack threads about 'when works for everyone?'\\n- Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\n- Social Proof: Used by 2,000+ distributed teams who've cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Companies like TechCorp save 15 hours per week on scheduling alone.\\n\\nREQUIREMENTS:\\nFor the Hero section, provide:\\n1. A powerful headline (8-12 words) that speaks to the pain point\\n2. A compelling subheadline (15-25 words) that explains the solution\\n3. Primary CTA button text (2-4 words)\\n4. Secondary CTA button text (2-4 words)\\n5. A trust indicator line (short phrase mentioning the social proof)\\n\\nMake it conversion-focused, benefit-driven, and speak directly to the frustration of coordinating meetings across time zones.\"}},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01VwZ4TW4zRoDXomQMC97AiD\",\"name\":\"task\",\"input\":{\"subagent_type\":\"copywriter\",\"description\":\"Draft compelling copy for the FEATURES section of a landing page.\\n\\nCONTEXT:\\n- Product: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones\\n- Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents. Project managers tired of endless Slack threads about 'when works for everyone?'\\n- Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\n\\nREQUIREMENTS:\\nFor the Features section, provide:\\n1. Section headline (5-8 words)\\n2. Section subheadline (10-20 words)\\n3. 4-6 key features, each with:\\n   - Feature title (3-5 words)\\n   - Feature description (15-25 words explaining the benefit)\\n   - An icon suggestion (simple keyword like \\\"clock\\\", \\\"globe\\\", \\\"calendar\\\", \\\"zap\\\", \\\"users\\\", \\\"check\\\")\\n\\nFocus on benefits over features. Address pain points like time zone confusion, endless back-and-forth, calendar conflicts, and wasted time.\"}},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01WA1w4uDL8ds2SfbHQkJZXp\",\"name\":\"task\",\"input\":{\"subagent_type\":\"copywriter\",\"description\":\"Draft compelling copy for the SOCIAL PROOF section of a landing page.\\n\\nCONTEXT:\\n- Product: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones\\n- Social Proof: Used by 2,000+ distributed teams who've cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Companies like TechCorp save 15 hours per week on scheduling alone.\\n\\nREQUIREMENTS:\\nFor the Social Proof section, provide:\\n1. Section headline (5-8 words)\\n2. 3 key statistics with:\\n   - The number/metric (e.g., \\\"2,000+\\\", \\\"80%\\\", \\\"15 hours\\\")\\n   - A short label (3-6 words describing what the metric represents)\\n3. 2-3 testimonial quotes from fictional but realistic users:\\n   - Quote text (20-40 words, specific and credible)\\n   - Name and title (e.g., \\\"Sarah Chen, VP of Operations at TechCorp\\\")\\n\\nMake the testimonials specific, credible, and focused on tangible results. Include details about time saved, frustration eliminated, or productivity gained.\"}},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01QjafbjDijstck9dizzSyCm\",\"name\":\"task\",\"input\":{\"subagent_type\":\"copywriter\",\"description\":\"Draft compelling copy for the CALL TO ACTION section of a landing page.\\n\\nCONTEXT:\\n- Product: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones\\n- Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents\\n- Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly\\n\\nREQUIREMENTS:\\nFor the CTA section, provide:\\n1. A compelling headline (6-10 words) that creates urgency or emphasizes the benefit\\n2. A supporting subheadline (12-20 words) that reinforces the value proposition\\n3. Primary CTA button text (2-4 words)\\n4. A trust/risk reversal line (8-15 words, e.g., \\\"No credit card required\\\" or \\\"Free for 14 days\\\")\\n\\nMake it action-oriented and emphasize how easy it is to get started. Remove friction and create urgency.\"}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Based on your scheduling tool context, here's compelling hero section copy that speaks directly to the pain of cross-timezone coordination:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headline\\\": \\\"Stop Playing Timezone Tetris. Schedule Meetings Instantly.\\\",\\n  \\\"subheadline\\\": \\\"Connect your calendar, set your preferences, and let us find the perfect meeting time for everyone—across any timezone, in seconds.\\\",\\n  \\\"primary_cta\\\": \\\"Start Free Trial\\\",\\n  \\\"secondary_cta\\\": \\\"See How It Works\\\",\\n  \\\"trust_indicator\\\": \\\"Trusted by 2,000+ distributed teams saving 15+ hours weekly\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Copy Rationale\\n\\n**Headline**: \\\"Timezone Tetris\\\" creates an immediate visual metaphor that remote teams will instantly recognize—the frustrating puzzle of aligning schedules. \\\"Instantly\\\" provides the aspirational outcome and creates urgency.\\n\\n**Subheadline**: Follows the simple three-step journey (connect → set → done) while emphasizing the key benefits: works \\\"across any timezone\\\" and happens \\\"in seconds.\\\" This directly addresses the pain point of endless coordination.\\n\\n**Primary CTA**: \\\"Start Free Trial\\\" is action-oriented and low-friction, perfect for converting motivated visitors who recognize their pain point.\\n\\n**Secondary CTA**: \\\"See How It Works\\\" provides a softer option for those who need more information before committing, reducing bounce rate.\\n\\n**Trust Indicator**: Combines social proof (2,000+ teams) with a concrete, relatable benefit (15+ hours saved weekly) that project managers can immediately quantify as ROI.\\n\\nThis copy speaks directly to the exhausted project manager who's tired of the \\\"when works for everyone?\\\" Slack threads and positions your tool as the instant relief they've been searching for.\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01K9nve8xGoXqSAfqGe9bcSz\"},{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Based on your scheduling tool context, here's compelling copy for your FEATURES section:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"section_headline\\\": \\\"Stop Scheduling. Start Meeting.\\\",\\n  \\\"section_subheadline\\\": \\\"No more timezone math, endless message threads, or calendar Tetris. Just instant meeting times that actually work for everyone.\\\",\\n  \\\"features\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Smart Timezone Translation\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Forget converting 3pm EST to Singapore time. Our AI instantly finds overlapping hours across all timezones, so nobody joins at 2am.\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"globe\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"One-Click Availability Sharing\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Connect your calendar once and we automatically share when you're free. No more screenshots of your week or 'let me check' messages.\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"calendar\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Instant Optimal Suggestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Get meeting time options in seconds, not days. We analyze everyone's calendars and preferences to suggest times that actually work for all.\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"zap\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Team Preference Learning\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Set your focus hours, no-meeting days, and preferred times once. We remember and respect everyone's working style automatically.\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"users\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Conflict-Free Scheduling\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Never double-book again. We sync with your existing calendar in real-time, blocking out meetings, lunch breaks, and personal commitments.\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"check\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"Async Decision Making\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Team votes on suggested times without another meeting about the meeting. First option that works for everyone wins automatically.\\\",\\n      \\\"icon\\\": \\\"clock\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key copywriting decisions made:**\\n\\n1. **Headline**: \\\"Stop Scheduling. Start Meeting.\\\" - Short, punchy, benefit-focused. Emphasizes the time saved.\\n\\n2. **Subheadline**: Directly addresses the three biggest pain points (timezone confusion, message threads, calendar conflicts) using conversational language your audience uses.\\n\\n3. **Feature copy approach**:\\n   - Each description starts with the pain point eliminated (\\\"Forget converting...\\\", \\\"Never double-book...\\\")\\n   - Uses specific, relatable scenarios (\\\"screenshots of your week\\\", \\\"2am meetings\\\")\\n   - Focuses on the outcome/benefit, not the technical feature\\n   - Conversational tone matching frustrated project managers' language\\n\\n4. **Icon suggestions**: Simple, universally recognizable icons that reinforce each feature's core benefit.\\n\\nThis copy speaks directly to remote teams drowning in scheduling chaos and positions your tool as the instant relief they need.\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01VwZ4TW4zRoDXomQMC97AiD\"},{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Based on your scheduling tool context, here's compelling social proof copy designed to build trust and demonstrate real-world impact:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"socialProof\\\": {\\n    \\\"headline\\\": \\\"Trusted by Teams Who Value Their Time\\\",\\n    \\\"statistics\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"metric\\\": \\\"2,000+\\\",\\n        \\\"label\\\": \\\"Distributed teams scheduling smarter\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"metric\\\": \\\"80%\\\",\\n        \\\"label\\\": \\\"Less time coordinating meetings\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"metric\\\": \\\"15 hours\\\",\\n        \\\"label\\\": \\\"Saved per week per team\\\"\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"testimonials\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"quote\\\": \\\"We went from endless email chains across three continents to one-click scheduling. Our engineering team now spends those saved hours actually building product instead of playing calendar Tetris.\\\",\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"Sarah Chen\\\",\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"VP of Operations at TechCorp\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"quote\\\": \\\"The timezone confusion alone was costing us deals. Now our sales team books client calls instantly, regardless of where they're located. It's like having a personal assistant for every rep.\\\",\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"Marcus Rodriguez\\\",\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Head of Sales at CloudScale\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"quote\\\": \\\"I used to dread scheduling our weekly all-hands with team members in Tokyo, London, and San Francisco. Now it takes 30 seconds, and everyone actually shows up because the time works for them.\\\",\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"Priya Patel\\\",\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Director of People Ops at DataFlow\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key copywriting elements used:**\\n\\n- **Headline**: Focuses on the value proposition (valuing time) rather than just saying \\\"what our customers say\\\"\\n- **Statistics**: Each metric pairs a concrete number with a benefit-focused label\\n- **Testimonials**: \\n  - Include specific pain points (\\\"calendar Tetris\\\", \\\"timezone confusion\\\", \\\"endless email chains\\\")\\n  - Mention tangible outcomes (building product, closing deals, better attendance)\\n  - Feature diverse roles (Operations, Sales, People Ops) to show broad appeal\\n  - Use realistic company names that sound like tech/SaaS companies\\n  - Stay within 20-40 word count for scannability\\n\\nThis social proof section builds credibility through specificity while maintaining authenticity.\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01WA1w4uDL8ds2SfbHQkJZXp\"},{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Based on your scheduling tool for distributed teams, here's compelling CTA copy that emphasizes ease and removes friction:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"cta_section\\\": {\\n    \\\"headline\\\": \\\"Stop the Scheduling Chaos. Start in 60 Seconds.\\\",\\n    \\\"subheadline\\\": \\\"Join 2,000+ distributed teams who've eliminated timezone headaches and reclaimed hours every week.\\\",\\n    \\\"primary_cta\\\": \\\"Get Started Free\\\",\\n    \\\"trust_line\\\": \\\"No credit card required. Free forever for teams up to 10.\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Alternative Options:\\n\\n**Option 2 - Benefit-Focused:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"cta_section\\\": {\\n    \\\"headline\\\": \\\"Your Last Scheduling Email Starts Here\\\",\\n    \\\"subheadline\\\": \\\"Connect your calendar once and never play timezone ping-pong again. Setup takes less than a minute.\\\",\\n    \\\"primary_cta\\\": \\\"Try It Free\\\",\\n    \\\"trust_line\\\": \\\"Free 14-day trial. No credit card. Cancel anytime.\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Option 3 - Urgency-Driven:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"cta_section\\\": {\\n    \\\"headline\\\": \\\"End Timezone Confusion Today, Not Tomorrow\\\",\\n    \\\"subheadline\\\": \\\"While you're reading this, your team is wasting time on scheduling. Fix it in under 60 seconds.\\\",\\n    \\\"primary_cta\\\": \\\"Start Now Free\\\",\\n    \\\"trust_line\\\": \\\"Instant access. No payment info needed to start.\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Why This Works:\\n\\n- **Headline**: Creates urgency (\\\"Stop...Start\\\") while emphasizing speed (\\\"60 Seconds\\\")\\n- **Subheadline**: Uses social proof (2,000+ teams) and quantifies the benefit (hours saved)\\n- **CTA**: Action-oriented, emphasizes \\\"Free\\\" to remove cost friction\\n- **Trust Line**: Double friction removal (no credit card + free tier) makes it risk-free\\n\\nChoose Option 1 for balanced urgency and ease, Option 2 for emotional resonance, or Option 3 for maximum urgency.\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01QjafbjDijstck9dizzSyCm\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent! Now I'll update the todos and create the components with this copy.\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01WFFEUzZYCQXyUHTY1i2hQf\",\"name\":\"write_todos\",\"input\":{\"todos\":[{\"content\":\"Draft copy for Hero section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Draft copy for Features section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Draft copy for Social Proof section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Draft copy for CTA section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Create Hero.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"},{\"content\":\"Create Features.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Create SocialProof.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Create CallToAction.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Create Footer.tsx component\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Assemble IndexPage.tsx with all components\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Verify all files are created correctly\",\"status\":\"pending\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Updated todo list to [{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for Hero section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for Features section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for Social Proof section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for CTA section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create Hero.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create Features.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create SocialProof.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create CallToAction.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create Footer.tsx component\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Assemble IndexPage.tsx with all components\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Verify all files are created correctly\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"}]\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01WFFEUzZYCQXyUHTY1i2hQf\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now let me create the Hero component:\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015m4jKfrNTh1FqCUf2T8KhS\",\"name\":\"write_file\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/src/components/Hero.tsx\"}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Tool 'write_file' failed after 3 attempts with ToolInvocationError\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015m4jKfrNTh1FqCUf2T8KhS\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me try again with the content parameter:\"},{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01AbbajL7DKwxE1JBaf8eSfh\",\"name\":\"write_file\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/src/components/Hero.tsx\",\"content\":\"import { Button } from \\\"@/components/ui/button\\\";\\nimport { ArrowRight, Play } from \\\"lucide-react\\\";\\nimport posthog from \\\"posthog-js\\\";\\n\\nexport function Hero() {\\n  const handleStartTrial = () => {\\n    posthog.capture(\\\"cta_clicked\\\", { section: \\\"hero\\\", cta_type: \\\"primary\\\" });\\n    // Navigate to signup or show signup modal\\n  };\\n\\n  const handleSeeDemo = () => {\\n    posthog.capture(\\\"cta_clicked\\\", { section: \\\"hero\\\", cta_type: \\\"secondary\\\" });\\n    // Navigate to demo or show demo video\\n  };\\n\\n  return (\\n    <section className=\\\"relative bg-background py-20 md:py-32 overflow-hidden\\\">\\n      {/* Background decoration */}\\n      <div className=\\\"absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/5 via-secondary/5 to-background\\\" />\\n      \\n      <div className=\\\"container relative z-10 mx-auto px-4\\\">\\n        <div className=\\\"max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center\\\">\\n          {/* Trust indicator */}\\n          <div className=\\\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-secondary/10 text-secondary-foreground px-4 py-2 rounded-full mb-8 animate-fade-in\\\">\\n            <div className=\\\"w-2 h-2 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse\\\" />\\n            <span className=\\\"text-sm font-medium\\\">\\n              Trusted by 2,000+ distributed teams saving 15+ hours weekly\\n            </span>\\n          </div>\\n\\n          {/* Headline */}\\n          <h1 className=\\\"text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6 animate-slide-up\\\">\\n            Stop Playing Timezone Tetris.{\\\" \\\"}\\n            <span className=\\\"text-primary\\\">Schedule Meetings Instantly.</span>\\n          </h1>\\n\\n          {/* Subheadline */}\\n          <p className=\\\"text-lg md:text-xl text-muted-foreground mb-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto animate-slide-up\\\" style={{ animationDelay: \\\"0.1s\\\" }}>\\n            Connect your calendar, set your preferences, and let us find the perfect meeting time for everyone—across any timezone, in seconds.\\n          </p>\\n\\n          {/* CTA Buttons */}\\n          <div className=\\\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center items-center animate-slide-up\\\" style={{ animationDelay: \\\"0.2s\\\" }}>\\n            <Button\\n              size=\\\"lg\\\"\\n              className=\\\"bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90 text-lg px-8 py-6 group\\\"\\n              onClick={handleStartTrial}\\n            >\\n              Start Free Trial\\n              <ArrowRight className=\\\"ml-2 h-5 w-5 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform\\\" />\\n            </Button>\\n            <Button\\n              size=\\\"lg\\\"\\n              variant=\\\"outline\\\"\\n              className=\\\"text-lg px-8 py-6 group border-2\\\"\\n              onClick={handleSeeDemo}\\n            >\\n              <Play className=\\\"mr-2 h-5 w-5 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform\\\" />\\n              See How It Works\\n            </Button>\\n          </div>\\n\\n          {/* Visual element - Calendar grid mockup */}\\n          <div className=\\\"mt-16 relative animate-fade-in\\\" style={{ animationDelay: \\\"0.4s\\\" }}>\\n            <div className=\\\"bg-card rounded-lg shadow-2xl p-6 border-2 border-border max-w-3xl mx-auto\\\">\\n              <div className=\\\"grid grid-cols-3 gap-4\\\">\\n                {/* Timezone cards */}\\n                <div className=\\\"bg-secondary/20 rounded-lg p-4 text-left animate-subtle-float\\\">\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-xs text-secondary-foreground-muted mb-1\\\">San Francisco</div>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-foreground\\\">9:00 AM</div>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2\\\">PST</div>\\n                </div>\\n                <div className=\\\"bg-primary/20 rounded-lg p-4 text-left animate-subtle-float\\\" style={{ animationDelay: \\\"0.2s\\\" }}>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-xs text-primary-foreground-muted mb-1\\\">London</div>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-primary-foreground\\\">5:00 PM</div>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2\\\">GMT</div>\\n                </div>\\n                <div className=\\\"bg-accent/20 rounded-lg p-4 text-left animate-subtle-float\\\" style={{ animationDelay: \\\"0.4s\\\" }}>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-xs text-accent-foreground mb-1\\\">Tokyo</div>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-accent-foreground\\\">2:00 AM</div>\\n                  <div className=\\\"text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2\\\">JST</div>\\n                </div>\\n              </div>\\n              <div className=\\\"mt-4 flex items-center justify-center gap-2 text-success\\\">\\n                <div className=\\\"w-3 h-3 bg-success rounded-full\\\" />\\n                <span className=\\\"text-sm font-medium\\\">Perfect time found for all 3 timezones</span>\\n              </div>\\n            </div>\\n          </div>\\n        </div>\\n      </div>\\n    </section>\\n  );\\n}\"}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Successfully wrote to '/src/components/Hero.tsx'\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01AbbajL7DKwxE1JBaf8eSfh\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01SCatZhfepqC1esqvDLr2wH\",\"name\":\"write_todos\",\"input\":{\"todos\":[{\"content\":\"Draft copy for Hero section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Draft copy for Features section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Draft copy for Social Proof section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Draft copy for CTA section using copywriter subagent\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Create Hero.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"content\":\"Create Features.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"},{\"content\":\"Create SocialProof.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Create CallToAction.tsx component with drafted copy\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Create Footer.tsx component\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Assemble IndexPage.tsx with all components\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"content\":\"Verify all files are created correctly\",\"status\":\"pending\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Updated todo list to [{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for Hero section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for Features section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for Social Proof section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Draft copy for CTA section using copywriter subagent\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create Hero.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create Features.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create SocialProof.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create CallToAction.tsx component with drafted copy\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Create Footer.tsx component\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Assemble IndexPage.tsx with all components\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"content\\\":\\\"Verify all files are created correctly\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"}]\",\"cache_control\":{\"type\":\"ephemeral\",\"ttl\":\"5m\"}}],\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01SCatZhfepqC1esqvDLr2wH\"}]}],\"system\":\"You are an expert landing page developer. You create high-converting landing pages that drive pre-sales signups.\\n\\n## Your Context\\n\\nYou have access to:\\n- **Brainstorm**: The user's idea, target audience, solution, and social proof\\n- **Theme**: 6 primary colors configured in tailwind.config.ts\\n- **Images**: Uploaded images including logos (from Cloudflare R2)\\n\\n## Your Tools\\n\\n1. **Filesystem tools**: ls, read_file, write_file, edit_file, glob, grep\\n2. **Copywriter subagent**: Use the task tool with subagent_type=\\\"copywriter\\\" to draft marketing copy before coding each section\\n\\nCRITICAL: When using write_file, you MUST provide both parameters:\\n- file_path: The absolute path (e.g., \\\"/src/components/Hero.tsx\\\")\\n- content: The COMPLETE file content as a string\\n\\nExample write_file call:\\n```\\nwrite_file(file_path=\\\"/src/components/Hero.tsx\\\", content=\\\"import React from 'react';\\\\n\\\\nexport function Hero() {\\\\n  return <div>Hero</div>;\\\\n}\\\")\\n```\\n\\nNEVER call write_file without the content parameter.\\n\\n## Workflow\\n\\n1. **Plan**: Break down the landing page into sections (Hero, Features, Social Proof, CTA, Footer)\\n2. **Draft copy**: For each section, use the copywriter subagent to draft compelling copy\\n3. **Code**: Create React components in /src/components/ using the drafted copy\\n4. **Assemble**: Create the main page in /src/pages/IndexPage.tsx\\n5. **Verify**: Read files back to confirm they're correct\\n\\n## Code Guidelines\\n\\n- Use ONLY shadcn/ui components from the template\\n- Use ONLY theme color utilities (bg-primary, text-secondary-foreground, etc.)\\n- Never use hardcoded hex colors\\n- One component per file, under 150 lines\\n- Add Posthog tracking to CTAs and signup forms:\\n  ```tsx\\n  onClick={() => posthog.capture('cta_clicked', { section: 'hero' })}\\n  onSubmit={() => posthog.capture('signup_completed')}\\n  ```\\n\\n## File Structure\\n\\n```\\n/src\\n  /components\\n    Hero.tsx\\n    Features.tsx\\n    SocialProof.tsx\\n    CallToAction.tsx\\n    Footer.tsx\\n  /pages\\n    IndexPage.tsx\\n```\\n\\n## Theme Colors\\n\\nAvailable CSS classes:\\n- bg-primary, text-primary, text-primary-foreground\\n- bg-secondary, text-secondary, text-secondary-foreground\\n- bg-accent, text-accent, text-accent-foreground\\n- bg-muted, text-muted, text-muted-foreground\\n- bg-background, text-foreground\\n\\nStart by exploring the existing template structure with ls and glob, then create the landing page sections.\\n\\nIn order to complete the objective that the user asks of you, you have access to a number of standard tools.\\n\\n## `write_todos`\\n\\nYou have access to the `write_todos` tool to help you manage and plan complex objectives. \\nUse this tool for complex objectives to ensure that you are tracking each necessary step and giving the user visibility into your progress.\\nThis tool is very helpful for planning complex objectives, and for breaking down these larger complex objectives into smaller steps.\\n\\nIt is critical that you mark todos as completed as soon as you are done with a step. Do not batch up multiple steps before marking them as completed.\\nFor simple objectives that only require a few steps, it is better to just complete the objective directly and NOT use this tool.\\nWriting todos takes time and tokens, use it when it is helpful for managing complex many-step problems! But not for simple few-step requests.\\n\\n## Important To-Do List Usage Notes to Remember\\n- The `write_todos` tool should never be called multiple times in parallel.\\n- Don't be afraid to revise the To-Do list as you go. New information may reveal new tasks that need to be done, or old tasks that are irrelevant.\\n\\nYou have access to a virtual filesystem. All file paths must start with a /.\\n\\n- ls: list files in a directory (requires absolute path)\\n- read_file: read a file from the filesystem\\n- write_file: write to a file in the filesystem\\n- edit_file: edit a file in the filesystem\\n- glob: find files matching a pattern (e.g., \\\"**/*.py\\\")\\n- grep: search for text within files\\n\\n## `task` (subagent spawner)\\n\\nYou have access to a `task` tool to launch short-lived subagents that handle isolated tasks. These agents are ephemeral — they live only for the duration of the task and return a single result.\\n\\nWhen to use the task tool:\\n- When a task is complex and multi-step, and can be fully delegated in isolation\\n- When a task is independent of other tasks and can run in parallel\\n- When a task requires focused reasoning or heavy token/context usage that would bloat the orchestrator thread\\n- When sandboxing improves reliability (e.g. code execution, structured searches, data formatting)\\n- When you only care about the output of the subagent, and not the intermediate steps (ex. performing a lot of research and then returned a synthesized report, performing a series of computations or lookups to achieve a concise, relevant answer.)\\n\\nSubagent lifecycle:\\n1. **Spawn** → Provide clear role, instructions, and expected output\\n2. **Run** → The subagent completes the task autonomously\\n3. **Return** → The subagent provides a single structured result\\n4. **Reconcile** → Incorporate or synthesize the result into the main thread\\n\\nWhen NOT to use the task tool:\\n- If you need to see the intermediate reasoning or steps after the subagent has completed (the task tool hides them)\\n- If the task is trivial (a few tool calls or simple lookup)\\n- If delegating does not reduce token usage, complexity, or context switching\\n- If splitting would add latency without benefit\\n\\n## Important Task Tool Usage Notes to Remember\\n- Whenever possible, parallelize the work that you do. This is true for both tool_calls, and for tasks. Whenever you have independent steps to complete - make tool_calls, or kick off tasks (subagents) in parallel to accomplish them faster. This saves time for the user, which is incredibly important.\\n- Remember to use the `task` tool to silo independent tasks within a multi-part objective.\\n- You should use the `task` tool whenever you have a complex task that will take multiple steps, and is independent from other tasks that the agent needs to complete. These agents are highly competent and efficient.\"}"
